 Here's the updated `EditDetailsScreen` code based on your requirements:

```dart
// File: lib/screens/edit_details_screen.dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:provider/provider.dart';
import '../providers/prayer_provider.dart';
import '../models/prayer_data.dart';

class EditDetailsScreen extends StatefulWidget {
  const EditDetailsScreen({Key? key}) : super(key: key);
  @override
  _EditDetailsScreenState createState() => _EditDetailsScreenState();
}

class _EditDetailsScreenState extends State<EditDetailsScreen> {
  int? _selectedYear;
  int? _selectedMonth;
  double _percentageCompleted = 0;

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    final prayerProvider = Provider.of<PrayerProvider>(context);

    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text('Edit Details'),
      ),
      body: Padding(
        padding: const EdgeInsets.all(16.0),
        child: Column(
          crossAxisAlignment: CrossAxisAlignment.stretch,
          children: [
            DropdownButtonFormField<int>(
              value: _selectedYear,
              items: [
                DropdownMenuItem(
                  child: Text('Select Year'),
                  value: null,
                ),
                ...List.generate(10, (index) => DateTime.now().year - index)
                    .map((year) => DropdownMenuItem(
                          value: year,
                          child: Text(year.toString()),
                        ))
                    .toList(),
              ],
              onChanged: (year) {
                setState(() {
                  _selectedYear = year;
                  _selectedMonth = null;
                });
              },
              decoration: InputDecoration(
                labelText: 'Select Year',
              ),
            ),
            SizedBox(height: 16),
            if (_selectedYear != null)
              DropdownButtonFormField<int>(
                value: _selectedMonth,
                items: [
                  DropdownMenuItem(
                    child: Text('Average for total year, or select month'),
                    value: null,
                  ),
                  ...List.generate(12, (index) => index + 1)
                      .map((month) => DropdownMenuItem(
                            value: month,
                            child: Text('Month $month'),
                          ))
                      .toList(),
                ],
                onChanged: (month) {
                  setState(() {
                    _selectedMonth = month;
                  });
                },
                decoration: InputDecoration(
                  labelText: 'Select Month',
                ),
              ),
            SizedBox(height: 16),
            Slider(
              value: _percentageCompleted,
              min: 0,
              max: 100,
              divisions: 20,
              label: '${_percentageCompleted.round()}%',
              onChanged: (value) {
                setState(() {
                  _percentageCompleted = value;
                });
              },
              onChangeEnd: (value) {
                if (_selectedMonth != null) {
                  prayerProvider.updatePrayerStatsForMonth(
                    _selectedYear!,
                    _selectedMonth!,
                    _percentageCompleted,
                  );
                } else {
                  prayerProvider.updatePrayerStatsForYear(
                    _selectedYear!,
                    _percentageCompleted,
                  );
                }
              },
            ),
          ],
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

Here are the key changes made:

1. The `_selectedYear` and `_selectedMonth` variables are now nullable (`int?`).

2. The year dropdown now includes a default "Select Year" option with a null value. When a year is selected, the `_selectedMonth` is reset to null.

3. The month dropdown is only shown when a year is selected (`_selectedYear != null`). It includes a default "Average for total year, or select month" option with a null value.

4. The slider's `onChangeEnd` callback is used to automatically save the data when the slider is released. If a month is selected (`_selectedMonth != null`), it calls `updatePrayerStatsForMonth` with the selected year, month, and percentage completed. Otherwise, it calls `updatePrayerStatsForYear` with the selected year and percentage completed.

5. The "Save" button and the list of months are removed since the saving is now handled automatically by the slider.

Make sure to update the `PrayerProvider` to include the `updatePrayerStatsForMonth` method, which should update the prayer stats for a specific month based on the percentage completed.

With these changes, the UI will show the months only when a year is selected, and the slider will automatically save the data for the selected year or month when released.

