 To display the variables set in the console on the home page, you need to ensure that the `PrayerProgressCardMaterial` widget is receiving the correct data and updating the UI accordingly. You can pass the `PrayerData` object to the `PrayerProgressCardMaterial` widget and update the UI based on the data.

Here's the updated `HomeScreen` code:

```dart
// File: lib/screens/home_screen.dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:provider/provider.dart';
import '../providers/prayer_provider.dart';
import 'prayer_progress_card_material.dart';

class HomeScreen extends StatelessWidget {
  const HomeScreen({Key? key}) : super(key: key);

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Consumer<PrayerProvider>(
      builder: (context, prayerProvider, _) {
        if (!prayerProvider.isDataLoaded) {
          prayerProvider.loadData();
          return Scaffold(body: Center(child: CircularProgressIndicator()));
        }

        final currentYear = DateTime.now().year;
        final currentMonth = DateTime.now().month;
        final prayers = prayerProvider.prayers;

        return Scaffold(
          appBar: AppBar(
            title: Text('Prayer Tracker'),
            actions: [
              IconButton(
                icon: Icon(Icons.edit),
                onPressed: () {
                  Navigator.pushNamed(context, '/edit-details');
                },
              ),
            ],
          ),
          body: Padding(
            padding: const EdgeInsets.all(16.0),
            child: Column(
              crossAxisAlignment: CrossAxisAlignment.stretch,
              children: [
                FutureBuilder<PrayerData>(
                  future: prayerProvider.getPrayerDataForMonth(currentYear, currentMonth),
                  builder: (context, snapshot) {
                    if (snapshot.connectionState == ConnectionState.waiting) {
                      return CircularProgressIndicator();
                    }
                    final prayerData = snapshot.data;
                    final totalPrayed = prayerData?.totalPrayed ?? 0;
                    final totalPrayersPossible = prayerData?.totalPrayed ?? 0 + prayerData?.totalMissed ?? 0;
                    return Column(
                      children: [
                        LinearProgressIndicator(
                          value: totalPrayersPossible > 0 ? totalPrayed / totalPrayersPossible : 0,
                          minHeight: 16,
                          backgroundColor: Colors.grey[300],
                          valueColor: AlwaysStoppedAnimation<Color>(Color(0xff34C759)),
                        ),
                        SizedBox(height: 8),
                        Row(
                          mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.spaceBetween,
                          children: [
                            Text('$totalPrayed'),
                            Text('$totalPrayersPossible'),
                          ],
                        ),
                      ],
                    );
                  },
                ),
                SizedBox(height: 16),
                Expanded(
                  child: GridView.count(
                    crossAxisCount: 2,
                    childAspectRatio: 1.5,
                    crossAxisSpacing: 12,
                    mainAxisSpacing: 12,
                    children: prayers.map((prayer) {
                      return PrayerProgressCardMaterial(
                        prayer: prayer,
                        year: currentYear,
                        month: currentMonth,
                        onPrayPressed: () {
                          prayerProvider.incrementPrayer(prayer);
                        },
                      );
                    }).toList(),
                  ),
                ),
              ],
            ),
          ),
        );
      },
    );
  }
}
```

In the updated code, we use a `FutureBuilder` to fetch the `PrayerData` for the current year and month. Once the data is available, we update the progress bar and display the total prayed and total prayers possible.

For the `EditDetailsScreen`, you can add variables at the top to set the start and end year. Here's an example of how you can organize it:

